Attributions
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This deployment documentation builds directly on the work of others. The
patches, scripts, and recipe here are integrations of, and small additions to,
the following:

- Zatz — the 655K DCP4 serving recipe, the MLA int32 chunked-prefill fix
  (patches/fix-mla-int32-chunked-prefill.py is his change, verbatim), and the
  context-vs-prefill dial. NVIDIA developer forum threads 375416 (posts
  12/13/15) and 374125 (post 112).

- CosmicRaisins — the sm_121 sparse-MLA port, kernels, and foundational
  GLM-5.2-on-DGX-Spark work. https://github.com/CosmicRaisins/glm-5.2-gb10

- ciprianveg — independent co-discovery of the DSA indexer block-table fix
  (NVIDIA forum thread 374125 posts 105/107; his mods/fix-dsa-block-table-dim).

- eugr — the spark-vllm-docker image build harness.

- local-inference-lab — the vLLM fork
  (branch codex/dcp-globaltopk-sharddraft-defaults-20260622) used here.

- voipmonitor — the b12x fork providing the sparse-MLA kernels
  (built from source at commit 9cd63a72).

- QuantTrio — the GLM-5.2-Int4-Int8Mix compressed-tensors checkpoint.
  https://huggingface.co/QuantTrio/GLM-5.2-Int4-Int8Mix

The GLM-5.2 model weights are subject to their own upstream license terms; see
the QuantTrio model card. Nothing here relicenses the model, the vLLM/b12x
forks, or the forum contributors' work — those remain under their respective
licenses and are referenced with credit.

New in this repository:
- patches/fix-mtp-draft-fused-qkv-mapping.py — first published fix enabling MTP
  speculative decoding on compressed-tensors (int-quantized) GLM-5.2.
- Independent co-discovery of the indexer block-table fix.
- First published c1-c6 concurrency numbers for this 655K recipe.
